{
  "texts": [
    "Over the past ten years, there has been a significant increase in the amount of Indian language material available on various media platforms, such as websites, blogs, emails, and chats where the growth of content is the result of individuals from small towns and non-metro locations.",
    "There is requirement to handle this massive amount of data automatically, especially in learning how the public feels about their operations and goods.",
    "The following points to get understand are discussed. Systems for recognizing entities in natural language are needed for this.",
    " There aren't enough benchmark data to compare the various systems now in use.In this article, contribution of several points which is mentioned below:  We discuss the taxonomy of NER approaches for Languages which is using nowadays such as Machine Learning (ML), Deep Learning (DL), Rule-based approach (RBA) etc.",
    "and also described the several algorithms of NER approaches."
  ]
}